                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363 Barco/70: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Piles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-24T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Your 2, January 18, 11 a.m. You should explain to the Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs that your Government was, of course, aware of the fact that the company
                    is a Colombian corporation, but that since practically all of the company’s
                    stock is held by American citizens the latter have a very real interest at
                    stake, and the Government of the United States perceived no impropriety in those
                    circumstances in inquiring through you at the instance of the stockholders
                    whether the courtesy of a reply to a memorial which had lain unanswered for 22
                    months might not shortly be expected.</p>
                <p>The Department approves of your taking the action suggested in the penultimate
                    sentence of your telegram under reference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
